 Motorists refuse to accept the Department of Public Works, Roads and Transport’s cavalier attitude towards the “sloppy work” done by contractors.
Millions of rands in taxes have been spent on rehabilitation, yet motorists are forced to risk their lives on a very treacherous road. www.mobserver.co.za has battled endlessly to milk out answers from the department on who the contractors are that were commissioned to do the rehabilitation, and how much money has been spent. The department’s response so far has only been to say that rehabilitation is complete and budgetary constraints withhold any repairs to the surfacing damages.
Broader inquiries have been made to the relevant authorities and www.mobserver.co.za now awaits their response. Read the full article in Friday’s copy of the Middelburg Observer.      Parents frustrated by a lack of space in Middelburg schools Traffic officers to appear in court for corruption #TrafficAlert: Two dead in Kranspoort accidents VIDEO: Two perish after truck jack-knifes • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za